complaints.summary: The front wheels are locking up sometimes when either hitting a bump in the road or just out of the blue while driving. The auto braking will engage quickly and then shut off.
2022 CADILLAC CT5. CONSUMER WRITES IN REGARD TO SHORTAGE OF COMPUTER CHIPS FOR VEHICLES HEATED STEERING WHEEL.

The contact owns a 2022 Cadillac CT5. The contact stated that while driving at an undisclosed speed, the Service Restraint System message was displayed. The vehicle was taken to the dealer where it was diagnosed that the driver's side air bag sensor needed to be replaced; however, the replacement part was on backorder. The vehicle was not repaired. The manufacturer was made aware of the failure. The failure mileage was approximately 3,500.

I purchased vehicle on 7/28/22 from Bayview Cadillac in Fort Lauderdale, Florida. On August 2, 2022, I noticed that my brakes were making a loud, harsh, scraping noise when coming to a full stop. Brakes also felt like they were going to lock up or stutter. On August 3, 2022, I brought the car back to the dealership to be serviced. On August 4, 2022, dealership told me that GM and Brembo (brake manufacturer) KNEW of this issue and were working on a bulletin to fix issue but that the bulletin would not be issued until late 2022 or early 2023. GM refused to take back vehicle in this dangerous condition with faulty brakes. Apparently ALL Brembo brakes across many different car manufacturers are having same issue. GM states it is "not a safety concern", however, the brakes are clearly faulty and dangerous. NHTSA should investigate this issue before someone is really hurt or dead.

Received message on dashboard 'Service Safety Restraint System'.  Dealership says that airbag needs to be replaced and it is not safe to drive the car.  Manufacture of the car does not have the part and cannot repair the car.  No timeframe on when the car can be repaired was given.    GM is already under investigation for this same exact issue from 2021 where 15 collisions resulted in airbags not deploying.

issues.title: Engine Oil Consumption Issues
issues.description: Reports of excessive oil consumption in the supercharged LT4 engine, requiring frequent top-offs between oil changes
symptoms: oil consumption rate above 1 quart per 1000 miles
issues.fix_description: Monitor oil levels frequently, engine teardown and piston ring replacement if severe
issues.prevention: Regular oil level checks, use recommended oil grade, avoid extended high RPM operation during break-in

issues.title: Carbon Fiber Wing Mounting Issues
issues.description: Reports of carbon fiber rear wing developing stress cracks at mounting points or becoming loose
symptoms: rattling or movement in rear wing
issues.fix_description: Replacement of carbon fiber wing assembly and reinforcement of mounting points
issues.prevention: Avoid aggressive aerodynamic loads, regular inspection of mounting hardware

issues.title: Magnetic Ride Control Suspension Failures
issues.description: Premature failure of magnetic ride control dampers, particularly front units, causing harsh ride quality
issues.fix_description: Replacement of failed magnetic ride control dampers with updated units
issues.prevention: Avoid harsh impacts, regular suspension inspection

issues.title: Cooling System Air Pockets
issues.description: Air pockets forming in cooling system causing overheating issues, particularly after service
issues.fix_description: Proper cooling system bleeding procedure, thermostat replacement if necessary
issues.prevention: Proper coolant service procedures, avoid low coolant levels

issues.title: Brembo Brake Rotor Warping
issues.description: Reports of brake rotor warping and judder, particularly on track-driven vehicles
issues.fix_description: Brake rotor resurfacing or replacement, brake fluid flush
issues.prevention: Proper brake bedding procedure, avoid prolonged heavy braking without cooling

issues.title: Fuel System High Pressure Pump Issues
issues.description: High pressure fuel pump failures causing reduced power output and fuel delivery problems
issues.fix_description: High pressure fuel pump replacement and fuel system cleaning
issues.prevention: Use high quality fuel, regular fuel filter replacement

issues.title: Infotainment System Freezing
issues.description: CUE infotainment system experiencing freezing and responsiveness issues
issues.fix_description: Software updates, module reset, or infotainment module replacement if severe
issues.prevention: Regular software updates, avoid system overload with multiple functions

issues.title: Differential Fluid Leaks
issues.description: Reports of rear differential developing fluid leaks at seals and gaskets
issues.fix_description: Differential seal replacement and fluid refill
issues.prevention: Regular differential service, avoid prolonged high-load operation

issues.title: Carbon Ceramic Brake Squealing
issues.description: Carbon ceramic brakes producing excessive noise during normal operation, particularly when cold
issues.fix_description: Brake pad replacement with updated compounds, rotor surface treatment
issues.prevention: Proper break-in procedure for carbon ceramic brakes, avoid low-speed hard braking

issues.title: Supercharger Belt Tensioner Failure
issues.description: Premature failure of supercharger belt tensioner causing belt slip and reduced power
issues.fix_description: Replacement of belt tensioner assembly and supercharger belt
issues.prevention: Regular belt inspection, avoid extended high RPM operation

editorial.tagline: America's last great supercharged sedan warrior
editorial.hero_blurb: The CT5-V Blackwing is Cadillac's ultimate performance statement - a 668-horsepower love letter to the naturally aspirated V8 era. This is your last chance to own a brand-new, manual transmission supersedan from a luxury brand.
editorial.essence: The CT5-V Blackwing represents the absolute pinnacle of American performance luxury, combining a hand-built 6.2L supercharged V8 with genuine track capability. It's simultaneously a gentleman's express and a circuit weapon, delivered with the kind of old-school drama that's rapidly disappearing from the automotive landscape.
editorial.heritage: Born from Cadillac's V-Series performance legacy, the Blackwing nameplate represents the brand's most extreme engineering efforts. The CT5-V Blackwing carries the torch from legendary CTS-V models, delivering supercharged American muscle in a sophisticated luxury wrapper.
editorial.design_philosophy: Cadillac's designers aimed to create a visually understated but functionally aggressive machine, with aerodynamic elements that serve performance rather than just aesthetics. The philosophy was 'stealth wealth meets track capability' - luxury that can embarrass supercars.
editorial.motorsport_history: While the CT5-V Blackwing itself is new to racing, it inherits DNA from Cadillac's successful ATS-V and CTS-V.R race programs. The platform benefits from extensive development in SCCA and Pirelli World Challenge competition.
editorial.engine_character: The LT4 supercharged V8 delivers explosive, linear power with a distinctive whine from the Eaton supercharger. It's muscular yet refined, building boost with authority while maintaining the smooth character expected from a luxury sedan.
editorial.transmission_feel: The available 6-speed manual offers precise, mechanical engagement with rev-matching technology, while the 10-speed automatic delivers lightning-quick shifts in Track mode. Both transmissions feel purpose-built for performance driving.
editorial.chassis_dynamics: The Magnetic Ride Control suspension delivers remarkable adaptability, transforming from luxury cruiser to track weapon at the touch of a button. The chassis balance is neutral with slight understeer bias, inspiring confidence at the limit.
editorial.steering_feel: Electrically assisted but tuned for feedback, the steering offers excellent on-center feel and builds weight naturally. Communication is clear without being harsh, perfect for both spirited driving and daily comfort.
editorial.brake_confidence: Massive Brembo brakes provide exceptional stopping power with excellent modulation and fade resistance. The pedal feel is firm and progressive, inspiring confidence during aggressive driving sessions.
editorial.sound_signature: A sophisticated growl at idle builds to a muscular roar under acceleration, punctuated by the distinctive supercharger whine. The exhaust note is purposeful and aggressive without being crude or obnoxious.
editorial.ideal_owner: Performance enthusiasts who want supercar capability in a luxury sedan package, collectors seeking the last of the manual supercharged breed, and drivers who appreciate old-school American muscle with modern refinement.
editorial.not_ideal_for: Buyers prioritizing fuel economy, those seeking subtle performance, anyone uncomfortable with the attention a 668-horsepower sedan commands, or drivers who prefer European chassis tuning philosophy.
editorial.buyers_summary: Act quickly - the CT5-V Blackwing represents the end of an era for naturally aspirated, manual transmission luxury performance cars. With values likely to appreciate significantly, early ownership is both a driving pleasure and potential investment.
